The '''''Companion to British History''''' ({{ISBN|978-0-9560983-0-6}}) is a single-volume encyclopaedic reference work "bigger than a foundation stone, longer than the Bible" (''[[Daily Telegraph]]'') written by [[Charles Arnold-Baker]] and in 1966 edited by his son Henry [[von Blumenthal]], who, as proprietor of Longcross Press, published the first and third editions. It was described as "arguably one of the most remarkable books ever written".<ref>http://www.spectator.co.uk/books/3299556/oneman-triumph/</ref> The second edition was by [[Routledge publishing|Routledge]].

