'''Tayopa''' is the name of a legendary [[Lost mines|lost silver mine]] in the [[Sierra Madre Occidental|Sierra Mountains]] of [[Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Marble |first1=Steve |title=Ray Dorr — adventurer, writer and keeper of the Kokoweef legend — dies at 88 |url=http://www.latimes.com/local/obituaries/la-me-ray-dorr-20170117-story.html |website=Los Angeles Times |accessdate=10 October 2018 |date=January 17, 2017}}</ref> Many stories, legends and myths surround it as well as articles and books describing the search for it. Folklorist [[J. Frank Dobie]] devoted part of his book "Apache Gold and Yaqui Silver" to the story of this legendary lost mine.<ref>{{cite | author = Dobie, J. Frank | title = Apache Gold & Yaqui Silver. Boston: Little | date = 1939}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Childress |first1=David |title=Lost Cities and Ancient Mysteries of the Southerwest |date=2011 |publisher=SCB Distributors |isbn=9781935487555}}</ref>
